            <title>[SOLR-12275] {!filters} are cached wrong</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-12275</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As it &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-9510?focusedCommentId=16452683&amp;amp;page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels:comment-tabpanel#comment-16452683&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;was spotted&lt;/a&gt; by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=dsmiley%40mac.com&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;dsmiley@mac.com&quot;&gt;dsmiley@mac.com&lt;/a&gt;, {&lt;tt&gt;!filters&lt;/tt&gt;} behaves wrong when cached. As a workaround it&apos;s proposed to pass &lt;tt&gt;cache=false&lt;/tt&gt; as a local parameter&lt;/p&gt;</description>
